npm install express mongoose bcryptjs jsonwebtoken dotenv
npm install --save-dev nodemon




auth-app/
│
├── config/                 # Database & environment config
│   └── db.js              # MongoDB connection
│
├── controllers/           # Logic for login, signup, logout, etc.
│   └── authController.js
│
├── middlewares/           # Middleware functions (e.g. auth check)
│   └── authMiddleware.js
│
├── models/                # Mongoose models (User schema)
│   └── User.js
│
├── routes/                # Route definitions (login, signup)
│   └── authRoutes.js
│
├── utils/                 # Helper functions (e.g. token, hashing)
│   └── generateToken.js
│
├── .env                   # Environment variables (PORT, DB_URI, etc.)
├── .gitignore             # Node_modules and env ignored here
├── package.json           # Dependencies and scripts
├── server.js              # Entry point
└── README.md              # Project overview (optional for now)








################# Files Names ################

| 📁 File / Folder                | 🔍 Purpose                                    |
| ------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------- |
| `config/db.js`                  | MongoDB URI se connect hota hai               |
| `controllers/authController.js` | Signup/login logic yahan likha hota hai       |
| `middlewares/authMiddleware.js` | JWT verify karne ka kaam karega               |
| `models/User.js`                | User schema (name, email, password, etc.)     |
| `routes/authRoutes.js`          | Routes like `/login`, `/register`             |
| `utils/generateToken.js`        | JWT token create karne wala helper            |
| `.env`                          | PORT, DB\_URI, JWT\_SECRET store              |
| `server.js`                     | App initialize, middlewares, routes use karna |

SPECIAL CODE FOR EMAIL IN USERS MODEL SCHEMA:

 /^\w+([.-]?\w+)*@\w+([.-]?\w+)*(\.\w{2,3})+$/,
 
